{"header":"<h1>Module type <code><span>MemVal.S</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":false,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../../../../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"soteria","href":"../../../../../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"Soteria","href":"../../../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Sym_states","href":"../../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Tree_block","href":"../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"MemVal","href":"../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"S","href":"#","kind":"module-type"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"","content":"<div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-S_bool\"><a href=\"#module-S_bool\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"S_bool/index.html\">S_bool</a></span><span> : <a href=\"../../../../Data/S_bool/S/module-type-S/index.html\">Soteria.Data.S_bool.S(Symex).S</a></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-S_int\"><a href=\"#module-S_int\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"S_int/index.html\">S_int</a></span><span> : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec type anchored\" id=\"type-t\"><a href=\"#type-t\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> t</span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec type subst anchored\" id=\"type-sint\"><a href=\"#type-sint\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> sint</span><span> := <a href=\"S_int/index.html#type-t\">S_int.t</a></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp\"><a href=\"#val-pp\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp : <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><a href=\"#type-t\">t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-merge\"><a href=\"#val-merge\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> merge : <span><span class=\"label\">left</span>:<a href=\"#type-t\">t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"label\">right</span>:<a href=\"#type-t\">t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Merges two children node into a single node; returns the merged node. Note children of the node are always preserved too, for further accesses.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-split\"><a href=\"#val-split\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> split : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">at</span>:<a href=\"#type-sint\">sint</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><a href=\"#type-t\">t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<span><span>(<a href=\"#type-t\">t</a>, <a href=\"#type-sint\">sint</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../Split_tree/index.html#type-t\">Split_tree.t</a></span> * <span><span>(<a href=\"#type-t\">t</a>, <a href=\"#type-sint\">sint</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../Split_tree/index.html#type-t\">Split_tree.t</a></span>)</span> <a href=\"../argument-1-Symex/index.html#type-t\">Symex.t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>split ~at node</code> Splits <code>node</code> at <code>at</code>, which is the relative offset within the node. Returns the left and right split trees, which themselves may contain further splits.</p><p><code>at</code> is guaranteed to be in the range <code>[1, size(node))</code>, i.e. strictly within the node.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec type anchored\" id=\"type-syn\"><a href=\"#type-syn\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> syn</span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-ins_outs\"><a href=\"#val-ins_outs\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> ins_outs : <span><a href=\"#type-syn\">syn</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><a href=\"../argument-1-Symex/Value/Expr/index.html#type-t\">Symex.Value.Expr.t</a> list</span> * <span><a href=\"../argument-1-Symex/Value/Expr/index.html#type-t\">Symex.Value.Expr.t</a> list</span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pp_syn\"><a href=\"#val-pp_syn\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pp_syn : <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><a href=\"#type-syn\">syn</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-to_syn\"><a href=\"#val-to_syn\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> to_syn : <span><a href=\"#type-t\">t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><a href=\"#type-syn\">syn</a> <a href=\"../../../../Soteria_std/Seq/index.html#type-t\">Soteria.Soteria_std.Seq.t</a></span> option</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Serialize this memory value; either returns <code>Some syn</code>, or <code>None</code> to signal the children must instead be serialized instead.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-consume\"><a href=\"#val-consume\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> consume : \u000A  <span><a href=\"#type-syn\">syn</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span><span>(<a href=\"#type-t\">t</a>, <a href=\"#type-sint\">sint</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../index.html#type-tree\">tree</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<span><span>(<a href=\"#type-t\">t</a>, <a href=\"#type-sint\">sint</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../index.html#type-tree\">tree</a></span>, <span><a href=\"#type-syn\">syn</a> list</span>)</span> <a href=\"../argument-1-Symex/Consumer/index.html#type-t\">Symex.Consumer.t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Extract the given <code>syn</code> predicate from the tree; this may result in an empty (<code>NotOwned Totally</code>) tree, or may only modify part of the tree if the predicate only represents part of this tree's state. A <code>Missing</code> may be raised if part of the state is missing for the consumption to succeed.</p><p>The input tree corresponds to the subtree relevant to the predicate's offset and length, meaning <code>t.node</code> is the node covering the whole predicate's range.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-produce\"><a href=\"#val-produce\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> produce : <span><a href=\"#type-syn\">syn</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span>(<a href=\"#type-t\">t</a>, <a href=\"#type-sint\">sint</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../index.html#type-tree\">tree</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span>(<a href=\"#type-t\">t</a>, <a href=\"#type-sint\">sint</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../index.html#type-tree\">tree</a></span> <a href=\"../argument-1-Symex/Producer/index.html#type-t\">Symex.Producer.t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Add the given <code>syn</code> predicate onto the given tree; the input tree is not necessarily empty (<code>NotOwned Totally</code>), and if the predicate overlaps the production may <code>vanish</code>.</p><p>The input tree corresponds to the subtree relevant to the predicate's offset and length, meaning <code>t.node</code> is the node covering the whole predicate's range.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-assert_exclusively_owned\"><a href=\"#val-assert_exclusively_owned\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> assert_exclusively_owned : \u000A  <span><span><span>(<a href=\"#type-t\">t</a>, <a href=\"#type-sint\">sint</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../index.html#type-tree\">tree</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(unit, <span class=\"type-var\">'err</span>, <span><a href=\"#type-syn\">syn</a> list</span>)</span> <a href=\"../argument-1-Symex/Result/index.html#type-t\">Symex.Result.t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Returns <code>ok</code> if this memory value is exclusively owned, ie no additional state can be composed with it; in other words, calling <code>produce</code> on a tree with this node must always vanish. Otherwise this should raise a <code>miss</code> with the fixes needed for this to become exclusively owned.</p></div></div>"}